      "message": "[Critical] Line 636: 🔴 Critical Issues - `myApp_ASSETS_CAR` is assigned `MACOSX_PACKAGE_LOCATION`, but it is not added to the macOS bundle target sources in this hunk. CMake only copies files with `MACOSX_PACKAGE_LOCATION` into the `.app` when they are part of the bundle target sources, so local/built app bundles can miss `Contents/Resources/Assets.car` and `CFBundleIconName\u003dAppIcon` will not resolve. Add the asset catalog file wherever `${myApp_ICON}` is passed to the `MACOSX_BUNDLE` target sources.\\n```suggestion\\n    ${myApp_ICON}\\n    ${myApp_ASSETS_CAR}\\n```",
